cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC

The paper discusses security weaknesses in shared web hosting servers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes countermeasures to secure the servers, which can be considered as software engineering (cs.SE). The attacks are server-side attacks, which involve network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system administration (cs.SI). The attacks also exploit the lack of proper isolation between different websites, which can be considered as distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
